FBIS4-27788 "dreas108__a94019" FBIS-EAS-94-108-A Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan Kakizawa Urges Arms Reduction Clause in NPT Kakizawa Urges Arms Reduction Clause in NPT OW0506123694 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN in Japanese 4 Jun 94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0506123694 Tokyo YOMIURI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa spoke in connection with the extension of the nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) at the House of Representatives' Foreign Affairs Committee on 3 June, and said the government will call for addition to the treaty of a clause requiring specific actions for nuclear arms reductions by the nuclear nations. He said, "We will ask for inclusion in the treaty of provisions clearly requiring nuclear nations to reduce their nuclear arms."
